{
  "abstract": "Conventional agriculture has been contributing significantly to several modern day\r\nenvironmental problems like global climate change, soil degradation, water pollution,\r\nbiodiversity loss etc. directly or indirectly. Organic agriculture has been identified as\r\none of the eco-friendly agriculture techniques and is being promoted worldwide to\r\nmeet the increasing demand for organic products and conserve the natural ecosystems.\r\nIt helps mitigating climate change through reduced emission of green house\r\ngases (GHGs), greater C sequestration and less use of fossil fuel. Besides, it has been\r\nfound helpful to reduce export of harmful agro-chemicals to water bodies,\r\nbiodiversity conservation, restoring soil health etc. Organic agriculture can help to\r\nmeet the objectives of sustainable and eco-friendly agriculture",
